to the editor the impact on the finances of older americans of this year 's prolonged slide of the stock market front page july 14 has all too often been a devastating tragedy i hope that this bear market will put a permanent end to discussions about taking some of the social security funds and investing them in the stock market far too many older americans rely on social security payments as their sole source of income in retirement they can not afford to have the government gamble with even a small fraction of that money frank ulrich southbury conn july 15 2002

